text: Ashley Elizabeth Priess (born March 8, 1990) is an American former artistic gymnast. She competed at the 2006 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships for the United States and earned a silver medal with the team. She attended the University of Alabama, where she competed for the Alabama Crimson Tide women's gymnastics team. While at Alabama the team won a gold, a silver and two bronze medals in the team competition at National Championships. She missed the 2011 season after double ankle surgery following the 2010 season. ==References== Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:American female artistic gymnasts Category:Medalists at the World Artistic Gymnastics Championships Category:Alabama Crimson Tide women's gymnasts Category:U.S. women's national team gymnasts
